-- Canada Names Blais as Chairman of Telecom Regulator CRTC
-- B y   A n d r e w   M a y e d a
-- 2012-06-08T20:10:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-08/canada-names-blais-as-chairman-of-telecom-regulator-crtc.html
     June 8 (Bloomberg) --The Canadian government named Jean-
Pierre Blais as chairman of the country’s telecommunications and
broadcasting regulator.  Blais, a former official at the Heritage Department, will
take over on June 18 as chairman of the Canadian Radio-
television and Telecommunications Commission for a five-year
term, the government said in a statement today on Prime Minister
 Stephen Harper ’s website.  Len Katz had been serving as interim chairman after the
five-year term of Konrad von Finckenstain ended in January.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Mayeda in Ottawa at 
